com.vmware.vapi.std.activation

Interface ActivationManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ActivationManagerTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActivationManagerStub

    public interface ActivationManager
extends Service, ActivationManagerTypes
    WARNING: Use only as a sample. The API is experimental and subject to change in future versions.

    Activation tracking/management service.

    An activation describes a method invocation in the runtime.

    • Method Detail

      • cancel

        void cancel(String activationId)
        Asks for cancellation of a running activation. Whether or not the cancellation request will have any effect depends on the implementation of the method that has to be canceled.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        activationId - activation identifier
        Throws:
        NotFound - there is no activation with the specified id

      • cancel

        void cancel(String activationId,
            InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
        Asks for cancellation of a running activation. Whether or not the cancellation request will have any effect depends on the implementation of the method that has to be canceled.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value. Use invocationConfig to specify configuration for this particular invocation.

        Parameters:
        activationId - activation identifier
        invocationConfig - Configuration for the method invocation.
        Throws:
        NotFound - there is no activation with the specified id

      • cancel

        void cancel(String activationId,
            AsyncCallback<Void> asyncCallback)
        Asks for cancellation of a running activation. Whether or not the cancellation request will have any effect depends on the implementation of the method that has to be canceled.

        Asynchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported via the specified asyncCallback.

        Operation Errors:
        NotFound - there is no activation with the specified id

        Parameters:
        activationId - activation identifier
        asyncCallback - Receives the status (progress, result or error) of the operation invocation.

      • cancel

        void cancel(String activationId,
            AsyncCallback<Void> asyncCallback,
            InvocationConfig invocationConfig)
        Asks for cancellation of a running activation. Whether or not the cancellation request will have any effect depends on the implementation of the method that has to be canceled.

        Asynchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported via the specified asyncCallback. Use invocationConfig to specify configuration for this particular invocation.

        Operation Errors:
        NotFound - there is no activation with the specified id

        Parameters:
        activationId - activation identifier
        asyncCallback - Receives the status (progress, result or error) of the operation invocation.
        invocationConfig - Configuration for the method invocation.
